ortunities for ALL the folks of Saryrn who might not otherwise get a chance. And, for the most part, I think we've done a fair amount to keep things this way, though we may not have been perfect.<br>
<br>
I'm not disagreeing with you, as I've noticed some of the same tendancies, but I'd like to put forth a couple of reasons why things might be a little more &quot;elitist&quot; right now...<br>
<br>
Training process - From discussion I've seen in the past, a majority of the reason why people have been suggesting SGA only events is for the training. One prevailing attitude is that we need to work together well, and become a cohesive team before we offer our services to everyone else. I believe the idea is that we won't do anyone else much good until we can get our own act together.<br>
<br>
Logistics - Since up until relatively recently, there's been no solid management of things, we really havn't had a decent way of getting organized on our own, nevermind for the non-SGA folks. <br>
<br>
With that said...<br>
<br>
Now that things are solidifying, IMO it's time that we make sure that we set down some good habits and make sure we don't fall into the UberGuild realm. <br>
<br>
Perhaps we should start bringing in folks from other guilds, or advertising our bigger raids on the Saryrn board...I'm not sure. But I think Hareq's pointed out a dangerous trend that's started that, if we're not careful, might turn into something we really would rather not have around.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE>